comment: From a cask, sweet and buttery, a bit of peat
Fantastic warm flavors with strong winters cinnamon notes. Goes down smooth on a summer day, but completes a holiday meal.
Very dark caramel flavors opening up to a soft finish.
Cinnamon on the nose, less sweet and grain then their bourbon. A little dry on finish.
Very fruity start with spicy finish
Brought it back from Frisco, CO.
Tasted like a bourbon with a little rye spice at the end. Pretty tasty
